Interpreter]]'' and ''[[Revelations (2005 miniseries)|Revelations]]''. He has also appeared as the mysterious villain [[List of James Bond villains#Film villains by production|Mr. White]] in the [[James Bond (film series)|James Bond]] films ''[[Casino Royale (2006 film)|Casino Royale]]'', ''[[Quantum of Solace]]'', and ''[[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]]''.\n\nIn his home country, Christensen has won four [[Bodil Awards]], three for [[Bodil Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|Best Actor]]: ''Did Somebody Laugh?'' (1978), ''[[The Bench (2000 film)|The Bench]]'' (2000), and ''[[Manslaughter (2005 film)|Manslaughter]]'' (2005), and one for [[Bodil Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|Best Supporting Actor]]: ''[[Barbara (1997 film)|Barbara]]'' (1997).\n\nIn 2006, Jesper Christensen declined the offer to receive the Knight's Cross of [[Order of the Dannebrog|the Order of the Dannebrog]]. He said that he thought the entire idea of monarchy is a crime against the members of the royal family, and it does not fit with modern ideas.<ref>[http://politiken.dk/kultur/article208462.ece Politiken, 5. dec 2006]</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role(s)\n! Director(s)\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1976 || ''[[Str\u00f8mer]]'' || Young Officer || [[Anders Refn]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1977 || ''[[Mind Your Back, Professor]]'' || Journalist || [[Jens Okking]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''Havoc'' || Steffensen || Ole Roos || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=4| 1978 || ''Wanna See My Beautiful Navel?'' || Fashion Photographer || [[S\u00f8ren Kragh-Jacobsen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''Who Kills Who?'' || Christian || Li Vilstrup || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''[[Winterborn (film)|Winterborn]]'' || Anders || [[Astrid Henning-Jensen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''Did Somebody Laugh?'' || Unemployed Man || [[Henning Carlsen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1979 || ''The Revolt of the Thralls'' || TBA || [[Jannik Hastrup]] || Voice\n|-\n| ''Charly & Steffen'' || Eigil || [[Henning Kristiansen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=3| 1980 || ''It's a World Full of Children || Morten || Aase Schmidt || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''Children of the Thralls'' || TBA || Jannik Hastrup || Voice\n|-\n| ''Sorry We're Here'' || Aage || [[Hans Kristensen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1981 || ''Have You Seen Alice?'' || Bjarne || Brita Wielopolska || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1983 || ''The Traitors'' || The Boy || Ole Roos || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1987 || ''[[Hip Hip Hurrah! (film)|Hip Hip Hurrah!]]'' || [[Viggo Johansen]] || [[Kjell Grede]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1988 || ''Emma's Shadow'' || Poul || S\u00f8ren Kragh-Jacobsen || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1990 || ''Today's Donna'' || Michael Nordgreen || Stefan Henszelman || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''[[Good Evening, Mr. Wallenberg]]'' || Officer at Watteau || Kjell Grede || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1992 || ''[[Sofie (film)|Sofie]]'' || Hans H\u00f8jby || [[Liv Ullmann]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1993 || ''[[The Russian Singer]]'' || Castensen || [[Morten Arnfred]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1994 || ''[[Carl, My Childhood Symphony]]'' || Schreiber || [[Erik Clausen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1995 || ''Summer'' || Flemming || Kristian Petri || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''White Lies'' || Kristian || [[Mats Arehn]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=4| 1996 || ''Girly Girls'' || Hans-J\u00f8rgen || Vibeke Gad || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''[[Hamsun (film)|Hamsun]]'' || [[Otto Dietrich]] || [[Jan Troell]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''The Ballad of the Viking King, Holger the Dane'' || [[Hemming of Denmark|Hemming I]] / [[Loki]] || Laila Hodell || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''[[The White Lioness#Adaptation|The White Lioness]]'' || Konovalenko || Pelle Berglund || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1997 || ''[[Credo (1997 film)|Credo]]'' || Brother 1 || [[Susanne Bier]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''[[Barbara (1997 film)|Barbara]]'' || Judge || [[Nils Malmros]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| 1998 || ''Albert'' || Shoemaker || J\u00f8rn Faurschou || &nbsp;\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1999 || ''[[In China They Eat Dogs]]'' || Bartender || [[Lasse Spang Olsen]] || &nbsp;\n|-\n| ''[[Sophie's World (film)|Sophie's World